WEBVTT

01:39.440 --> 01:43.270
[Road to Success]

01:44.780 --> 01:47.920
[Episode 18]

01:52.590 --> 01:54.190
How much longer will it take?

01:54.560 --> 01:55.600
Two hours.

01:56.420 --> 01:58.440
When's the next match
for your football team?

01:58.440 --> 01:59.870
It's not confirmed yet.

02:00.400 --> 02:01.590
When it is, let me know.

02:01.590 --> 02:02.590
I'll be with you for it.

02:02.590 --> 02:05.200
No problem. You can come anytime.

02:05.200 --> 02:07.000
As it happens, I'll be there too.

02:13.820 --> 02:14.980
What do you need?

02:15.000 --> 02:15.790
Tissues.

02:16.020 --> 02:16.680
I have some.

02:20.030 --> 02:21.030
Sorry about that.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.380
It's like you can read my mind.

02:29.840 --> 02:30.640
You need some?

02:32.270 --> 02:33.850
Thanks, mind reader.

02:37.430 --> 02:39.310
That's it for today.
Don't bother me again.

02:39.310 --> 02:40.710
I'm turning off my phone.

02:43.420 --> 02:44.820
Wake me up when we arrive.

02:45.240 --> 02:46.100
Take a nap then.

02:48.630 --> 02:50.630
It's worth taking this trip, right?

02:51.430 --> 02:52.360
Yeah, I suppose.

02:53.190 --> 02:54.190
You know what?

02:54.190 --> 02:55.520
I downloaded a lot of shows on my tablet.

02:55.520 --> 02:57.240
We can watch them together at night,

02:57.240 --> 02:58.310
in case you get bored.

02:58.310 --> 02:59.370
I won't get bored.

02:59.400 --> 03:01.400
I aim for a rest, I won't watch shows.

03:01.500 --> 03:03.760
It counts as a way of resting, doesn't it?

03:03.910 --> 03:04.430
Oh, right.

03:04.430 --> 03:06.030
About the mosquitoes,

03:06.030 --> 03:08.280
I'm fully armed with plenty of gear,

03:08.280 --> 03:08.960
plus

03:08.960 --> 03:10.400
a highly effective mosquito repellent.

03:10.400 --> 03:12.190
Foolproof. Nobody will get bitten.

03:12.190 --> 03:13.560
If by any chance you do get bitten,

03:13.560 --> 03:15.000
I'll feed the mosquitoes myself.

03:15.000 --> 03:18.190
Okay. Then take off your clothes
and feed them now.

03:19.470 --> 03:21.030
Right. Sure.

03:21.030 --> 03:23.360
You're driving. Eyes on the road.

03:39.120 --> 03:39.800
I...

03:41.740 --> 03:42.770
You're awake.

03:43.560 --> 03:45.240
You do know me well.

03:45.240 --> 03:46.320
Careful.

03:47.280 --> 03:48.750
Are you thirsty? It's chilled.

03:48.750 --> 03:50.840
Thanks. Just what I need
to refresh myself.

03:50.840 --> 03:51.750
Do you need my help?

03:51.750 --> 03:52.750
No, it's okay. I've got it.

03:52.750 --> 03:53.950
Just some more items.

03:53.960 --> 03:54.960
Let me carry this.

03:57.079 --> 03:58.120
It's okay. Hand it to me.

03:58.120 --> 03:58.750
I can manage it.

03:58.750 --> 03:59.360
Come on.

04:00.840 --> 04:01.870
According to Felix,

04:01.870 --> 04:04.430
Ms. Lin is your soon-to-be girlfriend,
isn't she?

04:04.430 --> 04:06.360
But it doesn't seem so to me. How come?

04:06.360 --> 04:06.870
Even Ms. Ju appears

04:06.870 --> 04:09.200
to be better boyfriend material than you.

04:09.710 --> 04:10.500
Felix!

04:11.680 --> 04:12.800
My sister needs your help.

04:12.800 --> 04:14.300
-Coming right up!
-Don't cause me trouble.

04:14.300 --> 04:15.220
You either.

04:15.840 --> 04:16.870
Mind the steps.

04:18.120 --> 04:19.250
Why not keep moving?

04:19.450 --> 04:20.310
Come on, hurry.

04:20.510 --> 04:21.310
Do be careful.

04:21.600 --> 04:22.140
I'll keep going.

04:22.140 --> 04:23.600
There's a lake over there!

04:24.250 --> 04:26.110
What are you standing here? Move!

04:26.120 --> 04:27.040
How can I let you carry it?

04:27.040 --> 04:28.100
Let me do it. Let me.

04:28.870 --> 04:30.120
You should never be bothered with this.

04:30.120 --> 04:32.580
-Seriously, give it to me now.
-I can manage.

04:33.120 --> 04:34.070
It's so heavy.

04:34.720 --> 04:35.360
Put it here.

04:35.360 --> 04:36.480
Okay.

04:36.480 --> 04:37.240
-Watch your hands.
-Is there any

04:37.240 --> 04:38.040
-tasty food?
-I'm all good.

04:38.040 --> 04:39.310
Let me do it. Let me.

04:43.730 --> 04:44.970
Braised food?

04:45.180 --> 04:46.800
All my favourites?

04:48.080 --> 04:49.120
Try them later.

04:49.120 --> 04:50.190
I made them myself.

04:50.190 --> 04:52.190
See if I got my dad's cooking skills.

04:53.159 --> 04:54.310
You made all these?

04:54.310 --> 04:57.570
I'm sure your cooking is nowhere near
as good as your dad's.

04:58.510 --> 05:00.610
So you two are childhood friends?

05:00.750 --> 05:02.880
Yes, we were desk mates in junior high.

05:03.160 --> 05:03.600
Wait.

05:03.600 --> 05:06.330
You're also a top student
returning from abroad.

05:06.560 --> 05:09.160
Why did you come to a small place
like Hongjing?

05:09.270 --> 05:11.950
Because Wanxing is here.

05:14.750 --> 05:15.870
So you're staying here

05:15.870 --> 05:17.750
for the same reason as Wang Fa's.

05:23.630 --> 05:24.160
Yeah.

05:29.830 --> 05:30.560
Time to pour drinks.

05:30.560 --> 05:31.720
Come on, let's have a toast.

05:31.720 --> 05:32.830
That's right. Time for drinks.

05:32.830 --> 05:33.390
-Come on.
-Come, let's drink.

05:33.390 --> 05:34.159
Don't just stand there.

05:34.159 --> 05:35.220
Come here, Wang Fa.

05:36.720 --> 05:37.390
Wang Fa, it seems

05:37.390 --> 05:38.560
to me that you're a bit

05:38.560 --> 05:39.620
distracted today.

05:40.560 --> 05:41.600
Alright.

05:41.600 --> 05:42.830
Come on, let's have a drink!

05:42.830 --> 05:44.760
The mind reader's here, isn't she?

05:47.390 --> 05:48.510
Let's take a photo together.

05:48.510 --> 05:50.040
Sure. We can print it out later

05:50.040 --> 05:51.680
and place it along
with our childhood photos.

05:51.680 --> 05:52.950
Now you look completely

05:52.950 --> 05:54.720
different from when you were a kid.

05:54.720 --> 05:56.600
And you're still as pretty as you were
in childhood.

05:56.600 --> 05:57.830
Such nice weather.
Why not have fun together?

05:57.830 --> 05:59.270
Stop taking pictures.

06:00.040 --> 06:01.300
Let's play a team game.

06:01.510 --> 06:02.370
Word guessing.

06:02.400 --> 06:02.950
You've all played it before, haven't you?

06:02.950 --> 06:03.830
I don't need to tell you the rules, right?

06:03.830 --> 06:04.330
Of course.

06:04.330 --> 06:05.310
-Yes.
-Pick a teammate.

06:05.310 --> 06:06.640
Let's split into teams.

06:06.830 --> 06:07.830
How about we two make a team?

06:07.830 --> 06:08.430
Sure.

06:08.430 --> 06:09.870
You and I team up then.

06:09.870 --> 06:10.800
I'll make sure we win.

06:10.800 --> 06:12.920
You? Are you sure you won't hold me back?

06:12.920 --> 06:14.950
Watch out, he might bring your score
into the negatives, Tian.

06:14.950 --> 06:15.830
I'll be your teammate.

06:15.830 --> 06:16.360
Okay.

06:16.390 --> 06:17.260
I object.

06:17.920 --> 06:21.000
-The three of us team up. We'll go first.
-You're not respecting the rules.

06:21.000 --> 06:22.800
I'll handle the countdown then.

06:24.720 --> 06:25.820
Are you ready?

06:26.000 --> 06:28.270
Three, two, one, action!

06:30.180 --> 06:32.150
[Rose]

06:30.600 --> 06:32.560
Four letters. I gave you
a whole bunch of these the other day,

06:32.560 --> 06:34.420
and you just threw them on my desk.

06:35.310 --> 06:35.950
[Rose]

06:37.560 --> 06:38.300
Pass.

06:38.330 --> 06:39.140
Tian,

06:39.159 --> 06:40.350
this is just a game.

06:41.770 --> 06:43.140
Fine, next one.

06:46.440 --> 06:47.450
You're familiar with this.

06:47.450 --> 06:48.530
Three letters.

06:48.140 --> 06:50.900
[KPI]

06:48.560 --> 06:50.270
You lash out on others about it
in every Monday meeting.

06:50.270 --> 06:51.220
KPI.

06:55.290 --> 06:55.659
[Theory of Relativity]

06:57.000 --> 06:58.950
It's your favorite Xi'an delicacy.

06:58.950 --> 06:59.560
What?

06:59.560 --> 07:00.830
Nonsense. That's not it.

07:00.540 --> 07:01.600
[Theory of Relativity]

07:00.830 --> 07:02.430
-A delicacy?
-It has a certain historical depth.

07:02.430 --> 07:04.230
It's actually available in Hunan as well.

07:04.230 --> 07:05.730
[Theory of Relativity]

07:04.430 --> 07:06.240
No, just ignore their nonsense.

07:06.240 --> 07:07.120
Whose team are you on?

07:07.120 --> 07:10.750
It's a physics term.

07:11.580 --> 07:13.000
He actually knows about physics.

07:11.720 --> 07:13.150
[Theory of Relativity]

07:13.240 --> 07:14.270
A pair-matching game.

07:14.270 --> 07:16.160
-Bumper rides?
-Say something.

07:16.160 --> 07:16.680
A tap-to-match game.

07:16.680 --> 07:17.920
There's no way to describe it.
You have to...

07:17.920 --> 07:19.270
Just explain it to him.

07:19.290 --> 07:20.270
It's just...

07:19.360 --> 07:21.550
[Theory of Relativity]

07:20.270 --> 07:20.950
We'll pass on this one.

07:20.950 --> 07:22.680
-Move on to the next.
-Fine, pass.

07:22.680 --> 07:23.410
Here it goes.

07:23.710 --> 07:25.540
[Dark Hole]

07:24.870 --> 07:25.830
I know this.

07:25.830 --> 07:26.720
It's a classic line

07:26.720 --> 07:28.430
of your sister's favorite cartoon

07:28.430 --> 07:31.040
in childhood, said by Pikaka's enemy,
the rocket squad.

07:31.040 --> 07:32.140
It's also an astronomical term.

07:31.850 --> 07:34.010
[Dark Hole]

07:34.600 --> 07:36.510
Your sister's favorite cartoon.

07:37.970 --> 07:40.450
[Dark Hole]

07:38.070 --> 07:39.720
Come on, what's wrong with y ou?

07:39.720 --> 07:40.600
I'll pass.

07:40.600 --> 07:42.200
Can you two step up your game?

07:45.270 --> 07:46.950
Listen, it won't be our fault
if you don't get this one.

07:45.480 --> 07:46.850
[Mona Lisa]

07:46.950 --> 07:48.950
You'll prove yourself a dummy
if you guess it wrong.

07:48.950 --> 07:50.040
Look, I'll make an impression of it.

07:50.040 --> 07:51.700
Alright. Three, two, one, go.

07:51.950 --> 07:53.310
It's a ceremonial greeter.

07:53.070 --> 07:53.940
[Mona Lisa]

07:55.720 --> 07:56.830
Looks like a shy young lady.

07:56.830 --> 07:57.920
Look at his facial expression.

07:57.780 --> 07:58.900
[Mona Lisa]

07:58.190 --> 07:59.390
The word is "creepy"!

08:01.160 --> 08:02.680
You think you're funny, huh?

08:02.680 --> 08:03.950
This is a painting.

08:04.310 --> 08:05.190
A painting?

08:05.950 --> 08:07.360
Two words. It's very famous.

08:06.040 --> 08:08.150
[Mona Lisa]

08:07.360 --> 08:08.690
"Terrible imitation"!

08:09.350 --> 08:10.240
It's in Paris,

08:10.500 --> 08:11.500
-France.
-Five.

08:11.240 --> 08:14.010
[Mona Lisa]

08:11.630 --> 08:12.630
-It's kept in the Louvre!
-Four.

08:12.630 --> 08:13.870
Three, two,

08:13.870 --> 08:14.950
-one.
-It's about a smile.

08:14.950 --> 08:16.510
-Time's up!
-This is over.

08:16.510 --> 08:18.630
It's Mona Lisa!

08:18.630 --> 08:19.870
My bad.

08:19.870 --> 08:21.770
You really are a dummy, bro.

08:21.800 --> 08:22.800
Alright, it's our turn.

08:22.800 --> 08:24.240
Let's show them what we've got.

08:24.240 --> 08:24.870
Get it started.

08:24.870 --> 08:27.070
Okay. Ready. Set, go!

08:27.720 --> 08:30.860
[Apple]

08:28.770 --> 08:30.710
It's a fruit.
There's a story of it and Newton.

08:30.710 --> 08:31.210
Apple.

08:31.240 --> 08:32.630
Yes.

08:32.669 --> 08:34.840
The ones you gave them are no-brainers.

08:34.840 --> 08:36.080
They drew these themselves.

08:36.080 --> 08:37.320
I didn't offer the cards to them.

08:37.320 --> 08:39.390
-Feel free to provide additional info.
-No, sorry, I was wrong.

08:39.390 --> 08:42.120
It's an animal you'd never see
in the North Pole.

08:39.470 --> 08:41.840
[Penguin]

08:42.120 --> 08:43.270
It walks like this.

08:44.090 --> 08:44.830
[Penguin]

08:44.200 --> 08:45.080
"Penguin."

08:45.080 --> 08:46.150
Perfect!

08:46.270 --> 08:47.810
[Schrödinger's Cat]

08:46.840 --> 08:47.960
It involves a box.

08:48.390 --> 08:50.000
This is my comfort zone,

08:50.000 --> 08:51.510
a famous quantum mechanics experiment.

08:51.510 --> 08:52.390
"Schrödinger's cat."

08:51.580 --> 08:52.290
[Schrödinger's Cat]

08:52.390 --> 08:53.270
Yes.

08:53.960 --> 08:56.360
People wear this to ward off

08:56.360 --> 08:57.720
-viruses.
-"Mask."

08:56.830 --> 08:57.580
[Mask]

08:57.960 --> 08:58.960
Yes!

08:59.720 --> 09:02.150
The only female emperor
in Chinese history.

08:59.860 --> 09:02.750
[Wu Zetian]

09:02.150 --> 09:03.000
"Wu Zetian."

09:03.000 --> 09:04.200
Yes.

09:04.200 --> 09:05.200
We are so in sync.

09:05.200 --> 09:07.550
It's used to describe
those starting strong but fizzling out.

09:07.550 --> 09:09.080
"All sizzle and no steak."

09:09.870 --> 09:10.550
A romantic experience.

09:10.550 --> 09:12.950
-Couples ride on these.
-"Ferris wheels."

09:30.480 --> 09:32.360
You still remember things
from eighth grade?

09:32.360 --> 09:33.630
Of course I do.

09:33.630 --> 09:35.440
I remember back then, in class,

09:35.440 --> 09:37.120
I often read Jin Yong's novels in secret.

09:37.120 --> 09:39.320
Thank God you were there to cover for me.

09:39.610 --> 09:40.750
Kids nowadays

09:40.750 --> 09:43.150
don't like reading Kung Fu novels anymore.

09:44.390 --> 09:46.650
I remember my grandpa would bring me here

09:47.120 --> 09:48.980
to fish every weekend in the past.

09:50.670 --> 09:52.150
There's fishing gear for rent here.

09:52.150 --> 09:54.480
If you want to fish,
we can come here again tomorrow.

09:54.480 --> 09:55.480
Really?

09:55.480 --> 09:58.280
Then the task of making fish soup
will be yours too.

09:59.240 --> 09:59.910
Not a problem.

09:59.910 --> 10:00.970
I'll throw it then.

10:01.600 --> 10:02.730
It's going too high!

10:08.790 --> 10:09.840
-My watch!
-Wanxing,

10:09.840 --> 10:11.170
don't get into the lake!

10:11.440 --> 10:12.910
I have to! That watch is a gift
from my grandpa!

10:12.910 --> 10:13.480
It's too dangerous.

10:13.480 --> 10:14.150
You can't get into the lake!

10:14.150 --> 10:14.880
But I have to!

10:16.480 --> 10:17.200
Wang Fa!

10:18.030 --> 10:18.750
Wang Fa?

10:19.480 --> 10:20.360
What happened?

10:22.600 --> 10:24.200
What's going on? Where is he?

10:24.750 --> 10:26.610
In the lake, looking for my watch.

10:28.080 --> 10:28.840
Wang Fa.

10:29.750 --> 10:30.440
Come back here.

10:30.440 --> 10:31.790
Stop looking for it!

10:31.790 --> 10:32.390
Wang Fa!

10:34.320 --> 10:35.150
Don't worry.

10:35.150 --> 10:36.600
He can handle the depth.

10:51.030 --> 10:52.240
-Wang Fa.
-I found it.

10:52.520 --> 10:53.710
Lin Wanxing,

10:53.830 --> 10:55.160
I found your grandfather's watch!

10:54.360 --> 10:56.680
♪ Life begins alone ♪

10:57.540 --> 11:00.110
♪ A road we walk alone ♪

11:02.110 --> 11:04.270
♪ Until fate brings warmth ♪

11:04.250 --> 11:05.130
Come back here now.

11:05.130 --> 11:08.450
♪ To light our way back home ♪

11:08.270 --> 11:09.550
Give me your hand.

11:10.360 --> 11:11.150
Be careful.

11:10.680 --> 11:12.340
♪ True love is not just ♪

11:13.140 --> 11:14.630
♪ The gaze when two hearts first meet ♪

11:15.570 --> 11:20.340
♪ It's courage in the arms ♪

11:22.380 --> 11:24.490
♪ We stand as one ♪

11:24.270 --> 11:25.030
Are you okay?

11:26.150 --> 11:28.050
♪ Our words flow ♪

11:26.390 --> 11:27.190
Yes, I'm fine.

11:29.270 --> 11:30.240
I found the watch.

11:29.770 --> 11:31.720
♪ A gentle stream ♪

11:33.920 --> 11:36.100
♪ They glow like fireflies ♪

11:36.750 --> 11:39.040
♪ Inside a silken dream ♪

11:41.830 --> 11:47.270
♪ We talk the cool night, breeze away ♪

11:49.430 --> 11:50.800
♪ We trace the roads ♪

11:51.420 --> 11:55.290
♪ That never see an end ♪

12:28.390 --> 12:30.320
Do you know how dangerous that was?

12:30.750 --> 12:32.040
It's a lake in the wilderness.

12:32.040 --> 12:33.610
Do you even know its depth?

12:33.640 --> 12:35.770
What if something had happened to you?

12:47.290 --> 12:48.240
Do you trust me?

12:55.830 --> 12:58.080
♪ Night slips through my fingers ♪

12:58.810 --> 13:02.940
♪ Embracing the coldness of wakefulness ♪

13:03.650 --> 13:05.540
♪ Whispering my thoughts alone ♪

13:06.130 --> 13:10.860
♪ Saying goodbye to the evening breeze
I chanced upon ♪

13:06.790 --> 13:08.790
Then nothing will ever happen to me.

13:11.620 --> 13:14.230
♪ Staying with the jasmine blossoms
until late spring ♪

13:14.940 --> 13:18.150
♪ Watching their elegance fade,
their fragrance disappear ♪

13:19.080 --> 13:21.870
♪ I once dreamed of something beautiful ♪

13:23.010 --> 13:26.970
♪ And I accept that
regrets may grow wild ♪

13:27.580 --> 13:30.120
♪ Look, beneath the sunlight ♪

13:28.320 --> 13:29.480
As for this watch,

13:30.080 --> 13:31.200
the only problem was the loose clasp.

13:30.580 --> 13:34.690
♪ In the dancing specks of dust ♪

13:32.240 --> 13:34.870
I just did a simple fix for you today.

13:35.290 --> 13:38.200
♪ I'm grateful I never lost my sincerity ♪

13:35.680 --> 13:37.480
There is no water damage.

13:38.290 --> 13:41.500
But still, you need to have it maintained
by a professional.

13:38.710 --> 13:42.500
♪ Or my gift for happiness ♪

13:41.530 --> 13:43.390
Or it might easily fall off again.

13:43.670 --> 13:46.070
♪ Sharing my warmth with a passing rain ♪

13:46.740 --> 13:50.600
♪ Quietly feeling its journey ♪

13:51.790 --> 13:54.210
♪ Like a firefly vanishing in an instant ♪

13:54.880 --> 13:58.590
♪ Still beautiful in its entirety ♪

13:59.450 --> 14:02.090
♪ There's no need to seek a final answer ♪

14:02.770 --> 14:06.540
♪ Let the ending remain with
questions unanswered ♪

14:07.340 --> 14:09.910
♪ No need to prove it with promises ♪

14:10.890 --> 14:14.650
♪ The dusk when we once vowed
to stay together ♪

14:15.600 --> 14:18.030
♪ No need to cling to forever ♪

14:18.540 --> 14:21.970
♪ Allow parting to happen quietly ♪

14:23.280 --> 14:26.180
♪ The inner voice hidden in the origami ♪

14:27.170 --> 14:32.670
♪ Each scratch and line
is proof of beauty ♪

14:29.670 --> 14:30.440
Wang Fa!

14:34.690 --> 14:35.500
Well...

14:35.940 --> 14:36.820
Sorry, I...

14:36.840 --> 14:38.040
T-This is about work.

14:40.080 --> 14:41.790
I'll go find Ju Li.

14:49.240 --> 14:50.150
What's the matter?

14:50.150 --> 14:52.150
Seriously, there's a message from the U.K.

14:52.150 --> 14:55.240
Kevin sold both his house and car
within just one day.

14:55.750 --> 14:56.750
Did you contact the club?

14:56.750 --> 14:57.790
Yes, I did.

14:59.000 --> 15:01.060
He's taken a leave and gone to Africa.

15:01.630 --> 15:03.550
When he's truly out of the country,

15:03.550 --> 15:05.390
even if we determine he's guilty,

15:05.390 --> 15:06.570
it'll be hard to hold him accountable.

15:06.570 --> 15:08.080
I'll ask my friends for help then.

15:08.080 --> 15:09.200
There's no time for it.

15:09.200 --> 15:10.080
Right now, book

15:10.080 --> 15:11.810
the earliest flight to the U.K.

15:12.670 --> 15:13.240
Okay.

15:14.790 --> 15:16.840
Then we have to leave now
and get on a plane tonight.

15:16.840 --> 15:18.000
Or we won't make it.

15:22.270 --> 15:23.720
Fine. You'll drive.

15:23.720 --> 15:24.980
I'll pack up the stuff.

15:25.030 --> 15:26.390
Got it. Okay.

15:29.170 --> 15:30.170
Where is Tian?

15:30.190 --> 15:32.370
She said she'd be busy for a while longer,

15:32.370 --> 15:34.230
and that we should go to bed first.

15:36.080 --> 15:37.320
-This is for you.
-Thanks.

15:37.320 --> 15:38.320
It's a bit too hot.

15:42.840 --> 15:43.670
Wanxing,

15:44.320 --> 15:46.320
actually, it has been a long time

15:46.320 --> 15:47.340
since I was this happy.

15:47.340 --> 15:48.170
Me too.

15:48.960 --> 15:50.290
I'm also very happy now.

15:58.360 --> 15:59.200
Oh right.

16:00.080 --> 16:01.200
That man Wang Fa...

16:03.270 --> 16:04.660
Are you into him?

16:10.670 --> 16:11.720
Ms. Lin.

16:15.320 --> 16:16.580
Excuse me for a moment.

16:29.440 --> 16:30.440
Sorry.

16:30.440 --> 16:31.570
You are leaving now?

16:31.590 --> 16:32.590
In such a rush?

16:32.790 --> 16:33.790
Time is pressing.

16:34.150 --> 16:36.150
I have to fly back to the U.K. tonight.

16:36.150 --> 16:37.950
Is it because of Jason's matter?

16:38.870 --> 16:40.510
The investigation has taken
a new direction.

16:40.510 --> 16:42.710
I need to get back there and deal with it.

16:44.910 --> 16:46.770
I'll wait till you come back then.

16:49.150 --> 16:51.040
Keep me updated on any developments

16:51.040 --> 16:52.240
of the football team.

16:53.020 --> 16:53.980
Don't worry.

16:54.270 --> 16:55.470
I'm here for the team.

16:57.080 --> 16:58.340
Take care of yourself.

17:05.069 --> 17:05.750
Bye.

17:10.420 --> 17:15.890
♪ Waiting for a dark cloud
to pass by you ♪

17:17.140 --> 17:21.470
♪ Listen closely to its cries ♪

17:23.510 --> 17:28.590
♪ The heavy rain will wash away
your reflection ♪

17:29.620 --> 17:34.610
♪ And carry it toward distant scenery ♪

17:36.460 --> 17:42.090
♪ Every experience has its meaning ♪

17:43.060 --> 17:47.480
♪ Scene by scene, they come together
to form who I am ♪

17:45.650 --> 17:46.610
Grandpa,

17:46.940 --> 17:47.980
today,

17:48.000 --> 17:50.590
I almost lost your watch.

17:49.450 --> 17:54.740
♪ Even the wounds
that leave behind their marks ♪

17:50.680 --> 17:52.410
But Wang Fa found it back for me.

17:53.370 --> 17:54.330
I've decided

17:54.350 --> 17:55.930
to put it away for safekeeping.

17:55.790 --> 18:00.340
♪ Have taught me how to heal myself ♪

17:56.500 --> 17:57.490
Grandpa,

17:57.830 --> 17:59.000
don't worry.

17:59.310 --> 18:00.440
Just like you,

18:00.730 --> 18:02.460
he treats me very, very well.

18:01.350 --> 18:07.130
♪ The love I have given,
the love I have received ♪

18:04.220 --> 18:04.950
[London Heathrow Airport]

18:04.980 --> 18:08.900
[London, U.K.]

18:07.960 --> 18:10.730
♪ Every bit of it makes me ♪

18:09.680 --> 18:11.740
Based on the information we have now,

18:12.550 --> 18:15.030
Kevin probably got in contact with Spade Q

18:15.030 --> 18:16.690
through some sort of channel,

18:17.400 --> 18:19.310
and then hired him to frame Jason.

18:21.550 --> 18:23.160
Yeah, but you have no evidence

18:23.160 --> 18:24.770
to support this claim.

18:29.270 --> 18:30.160
What if...

18:31.510 --> 18:32.910
we pretend to have proof?

18:34.770 --> 18:35.970
You mean to bluff him?

18:37.590 --> 18:40.010
Our goal is to get Kevin's confession

18:40.160 --> 18:41.070
and obtain evidence

18:41.070 --> 18:42.790
about Spade Q from him.

18:43.070 --> 18:43.720
If we use

18:43.720 --> 18:45.720
the existing clues to bluff him now,

18:45.720 --> 18:47.200
it might get us what we want.

18:47.200 --> 18:48.160
I-I understand.

18:48.160 --> 18:50.310
But if we are to cook up fake proof

18:50.310 --> 18:51.680
with existing clues,

18:52.110 --> 18:53.790
there had better be a logic to follow.

18:53.790 --> 18:54.960
The problem is that we don't have it now.

18:54.960 --> 18:56.760
The clues are all disconnected.

18:57.910 --> 18:59.910
If Kevin did employ Spade Q,

19:00.430 --> 19:02.190
there must've been payments.

19:02.260 --> 19:03.770
I'll check their bank accounts then.

19:03.770 --> 19:04.570
No.

19:04.680 --> 19:06.160
Spade Q works with great caution

19:06.160 --> 19:07.640
and never leaves a trail.

19:07.640 --> 19:09.840
He'd definitely choose the safest way—

19:09.920 --> 19:11.650
settling the payments in cash.

19:12.550 --> 19:13.400
That's right.

19:23.820 --> 19:24.600
[It rained all day today. A bit cold, too]

19:24.630 --> 19:25.570
[Spade Q said she hates
going out when it rains. So do I]

19:25.600 --> 19:26.590
[It feels good to train
in the rain, though]

19:31.040 --> 19:31.810
Look at this.

19:40.110 --> 19:41.240
I'll look into the weather data

19:41.240 --> 19:42.600
in London from a year ago.

19:42.600 --> 19:43.730
Oh, there's more.

19:43.750 --> 19:45.820
I'll also sot out
all the match procedures,

19:45.820 --> 19:47.080
meetings, and events

19:47.110 --> 19:48.370
in Hammer Club for you.

19:49.550 --> 19:50.610
I get what you mean.

20:07.900 --> 20:10.750
[Analysis of the key players' techniques]

20:17.730 --> 20:19.130
[Training Plans
for Hongjing No. 8 High School]

20:26.070 --> 20:28.720
With a time difference of seven hours,

20:29.240 --> 20:33.000
it's 3:30 p.m. in London.

20:34.200 --> 20:36.110
Could he be busy right now?

20:41.500 --> 20:43.150
[Winfred] [Inviting you for a voicecall]

20:48.790 --> 20:49.480
Hello.

20:49.840 --> 20:50.510
Hello.

20:52.070 --> 20:53.400
Have you gone to bed yet?

20:55.000 --> 20:55.730
Take a guess.

20:57.590 --> 20:59.390
I guess you're still up, Ms. Lin.

21:00.000 --> 21:02.600
You must be reading materials
about the match.

21:02.620 --> 21:05.350
Did you install a surveillance camera
at my home?

21:08.070 --> 21:10.400
I'm studying Yuzhou Yinxiang's tactics.

21:10.400 --> 21:13.440
And I've discovered
that they have strong defense.

21:13.650 --> 21:14.510
Coach Wang,

21:14.510 --> 21:17.370
how about sharing your thoughts
with me on tactics?

21:18.590 --> 21:20.250
They really are a strong team.

21:21.110 --> 21:23.760
Yinxiang adopts a highly compact
defensive strategy.

21:23.760 --> 21:25.760
The players are all tall and strong.

21:25.920 --> 21:26.790
However, because of this,

21:26.790 --> 21:29.390
they tend to lack flexibility
in positioning.

21:29.720 --> 21:31.850
I do have an idea
about how to defeat them.

21:31.850 --> 21:32.600
Great.

21:32.750 --> 21:33.440
Wait a second.

21:33.440 --> 21:34.920
I'll grab a pen to take notes.

21:34.920 --> 21:35.720
Okay.

21:38.200 --> 21:38.920
Go ahead.

21:39.140 --> 21:41.090
Since the opponent is strong in defense,

21:41.090 --> 21:42.690
in the first half of the game,

21:42.750 --> 21:44.240
we shouldn't put all our energy

21:44.240 --> 21:45.440
into going on the offensive.

21:45.440 --> 21:47.190
Instead, we should put up a defense.

21:47.190 --> 21:48.920
Then, we'll set up some decoy attacks

21:48.920 --> 21:51.780
to drain the opponent's energy
as much as possible.

21:51.920 --> 21:53.350
So in the recent training sessions,

21:53.350 --> 21:54.640
remind our players of having more practice

21:54.640 --> 21:55.790
on breaking through compact defense.

21:55.790 --> 21:57.000
Hold on, wait.

21:57.000 --> 21:57.900
Slow slower.

21:57.920 --> 21:58.980
I can't keep up with my notes.

21:58.980 --> 21:59.740
Okay.

22:01.310 --> 22:02.240
About the training,

22:02.240 --> 22:03.640
tell the boys to have

22:03.640 --> 22:04.240
more practice

22:04.240 --> 22:06.370
vertical penetration and set pieces.

22:07.070 --> 22:08.640
Okay. Notes taken.

22:10.400 --> 22:13.130
I'll be waiting for news of victory then,
Ms. Lin.

22:14.510 --> 22:15.550
Thank you.

22:16.550 --> 22:17.380
Hold on.

22:17.790 --> 22:20.350
When will you be back...

22:23.550 --> 22:27.310
to check out the team's training results?

22:30.020 --> 22:30.820
Very soon.

22:39.090 --> 22:40.170
Do come back soon.

22:40.720 --> 22:41.860
Yellow would like to

22:42.040 --> 22:43.470
play with Orange again.

22:44.050 --> 22:45.350
Once my work's done here,

22:45.350 --> 22:46.410
I'll be right back.

22:48.780 --> 22:49.570
Good night.

23:01.260 --> 23:04.770
[Strategies against Yuzhou Yinxiang]

23:07.450 --> 23:09.280
Come on, let's discuss

23:09.310 --> 23:11.510
what tactics to take for the next match.

23:13.070 --> 23:14.330
What did the coach say?

23:14.720 --> 23:15.520
He said

23:15.550 --> 23:18.950
that independent thinking is also part
of the team's growth.

23:20.790 --> 23:22.920
If you ask me, it's quite simple.

23:22.920 --> 23:25.550
We adhered to only one principle
when we defeated Lyujing last time—

23:25.550 --> 23:27.030
defense before offense, right?

23:26.510 --> 23:31.490
[Strategies against Yuzhou Yinxiang]

23:27.030 --> 23:29.000
This time, let's just do the same thing.

23:29.000 --> 23:31.240
I'm sure we'll crush them right away.

23:32.080 --> 23:33.810
-I agree with you, Boss.
-We...

23:34.030 --> 23:35.550
Coach Wang has told us many times

23:35.550 --> 23:37.200
to use our brains when we play, hasn't he?

23:37.200 --> 23:38.600
Where's your brain, bro?

23:38.750 --> 23:40.350
You're criticizing me then?

23:40.440 --> 23:41.000
Using the same tactic

23:41.000 --> 23:42.060
simply just won't do.

23:42.060 --> 23:43.750
How about we try
pressing high up the pitch?

23:42.120 --> 23:46.370
[Strategies against Yuzhou Yinxiang]

23:44.030 --> 23:44.920
No, we can't do that.

23:44.920 --> 23:46.030
Few players will be left
in the backcourt, right?

23:46.030 --> 23:47.680
Feng Suo will be under tremendous pressure
in defense.

23:46.430 --> 23:50.800
[1 Defense before offense]

23:47.680 --> 23:49.790
Right, I'll become an easy target.

23:49.790 --> 23:51.550
In my opinion, guys,

23:51.550 --> 23:54.640
just listen to me. Assuming the defensive
before offensive will really work.

23:53.940 --> 23:57.840
[1 Defense before offense]
[2 Pressing high up the pitch]

23:54.640 --> 23:56.000
I know what you're concerned about,

23:56.000 --> 23:56.920
that the opposing players are strong

23:56.920 --> 23:58.070
physically and in defense.

23:58.070 --> 24:00.000
But Chen and I aren't half bad.

24:00.000 --> 24:01.790
I say we should attack from both flanks.

24:01.790 --> 24:03.070
It's the best option for the team we have,

24:03.070 --> 24:04.550
as it reduces the pressure
on the midfielders.

24:04.550 --> 24:05.440
When we stretch on both sides,

24:05.440 --> 24:06.400
our formation can cover a wider space.

24:06.400 --> 24:07.310
But, you see,

24:07.750 --> 24:09.240
Chen's on the right flank,

24:09.240 --> 24:10.920
while I'm the centre-forward.
Who should take the left then?

24:10.920 --> 24:12.310
Ming can be placed there.

24:12.310 --> 24:12.550
Yeah.

24:12.550 --> 24:13.510
He moves fast.

24:13.510 --> 24:16.000
Fast speed, but weak body, bro.

24:14.050 --> 24:17.410
[Robert's Rules of Order]

24:16.000 --> 24:17.730
Indeed, he can't take the heat.

24:18.960 --> 24:21.120
W-What does that mean?

24:20.820 --> 24:22.830
[Robert's Rules of Order]

24:21.400 --> 24:23.720
-Robert's Rules of Order.
-Rules.

24:23.720 --> 24:26.270
These rules secure
efficient and orderly discussions,

24:26.270 --> 24:29.030
and ensure full participation
and democratic decision-making.

24:29.030 --> 24:31.200
In short, there are four steps.

24:31.200 --> 24:33.160
First, propose a motion.

24:33.160 --> 24:34.000
By doing so,

24:34.000 --> 24:36.070
attendees raise opinions and suggestions

24:36.070 --> 24:37.880
regarding a specific matter.

24:37.880 --> 24:39.640
Next, second the motion.

24:39.640 --> 24:40.640
As long as one of the attendees

24:40.640 --> 24:43.310
would like to discuss the motion proposed,

24:43.310 --> 24:45.160
whether the others are for or against it,

24:45.160 --> 24:47.310
we can enter the third step directly.

24:48.160 --> 24:50.240
Now, you've done the first two steps.

24:50.240 --> 24:51.000
Next,

24:51.000 --> 24:52.750
we can move onto the third step—

24:52.750 --> 24:53.480
discussion.

24:53.830 --> 24:56.510
All attendees have the right to voice

24:56.510 --> 24:58.710
their opinions fully about the motion.

25:02.030 --> 25:02.760
Let's begin.

25:07.160 --> 25:09.480
Ms. Lin, I already shared my views.

25:11.270 --> 25:12.550
Who else would like to speak?

25:12.550 --> 25:13.400
Ms. Lin!

25:15.240 --> 25:16.480
I did the math.

25:16.640 --> 25:18.310
In several games
Yinxiang played previously,

25:18.310 --> 25:19.790
60% of their conceded goals

25:19.790 --> 25:22.960
happened after their opponents
launched more than three attacks.

25:22.960 --> 25:24.270
Therefore, I think

25:24.270 --> 25:27.110
perhaps the Total Football approach
suits us better.

25:26.990 --> 25:30.850
[1 Defense before offense] [2 Pressing
high up the pitch] [3 Total Football]

25:28.240 --> 25:29.440
I don't think the strategy of assuming

25:29.440 --> 25:31.400
the defensive before offensive
is a good fit for this match.

25:31.400 --> 25:32.750
Look, our opponents are all big and tall.

25:32.750 --> 25:33.920
We can't outmuscle them.

25:33.920 --> 25:35.790
Let's put Feng Suo in defense in the back,

25:35.790 --> 25:37.780
and have two or three players...

25:50.350 --> 25:51.310
The Total Football approach

25:51.310 --> 25:53.640
requires higher flexibility
from the wingers.

25:53.640 --> 25:57.240
Actually, it can reduce the pressure
on the midfielders by a lot.

26:08.480 --> 26:09.720
We were able to defeat Lyujing

26:09.720 --> 26:11.780
because they focus on
launching quick attacks.

26:11.780 --> 26:14.000
But all Yinxiang players
are tall and strong,

26:14.000 --> 26:15.270
especially their defenders,

26:15.270 --> 26:17.420
which contributes to
their excellent defense.

26:17.420 --> 26:19.350
If we fight a war of attrition with them,

26:19.350 --> 26:21.000
we surely won't stand a chance of winning.

26:21.000 --> 26:22.350
So, my suggestion

26:22.370 --> 26:23.750
is that we should learn from Lyujing,

26:23.750 --> 26:24.830
initiate attacks,

26:24.830 --> 26:26.160
and go for high-intensity pressing.

26:26.160 --> 26:28.480
Only when we disrupt their pace first
will we stand a chance of winning.

26:28.480 --> 26:31.000
-What's there to learn from a loser?
-That is to...

26:31.000 --> 26:31.790
Qin Ao.

26:32.350 --> 26:33.350
No interruption.

26:35.510 --> 26:36.790
Whether a tactic works

26:36.790 --> 26:38.400
depends on the people using it.

26:38.400 --> 26:39.200
I'm finished.

26:44.300 --> 26:46.740
[1 Defense before offense]
[2 Pressing high up the pitch]

26:46.540 --> 26:47.880
Does anyone else have any opinions?

26:46.760 --> 26:49.320
[3 Total Football]
[4 High-intensity pressing]

26:47.880 --> 26:48.350
No.

26:48.350 --> 26:49.510
No, Ms. Lin.

26:51.070 --> 26:52.270
Then let's take a vote.

26:52.270 --> 26:53.310
Each attendee has one vote.

26:53.310 --> 26:54.920
The majority rules.

26:54.920 --> 26:56.250
No objections allowed.

27:08.640 --> 27:09.590
Six votes.

27:11.270 --> 27:13.640
I believe you've all seen the result.

27:13.640 --> 27:16.030
This concludes today's class.

27:16.030 --> 27:17.000
Ms. Lin,

27:17.510 --> 27:18.480
did you teach us this

27:18.480 --> 27:20.310
so you could slack off and let us discuss

27:20.310 --> 27:22.110
and decide on every matter ourselves

27:22.110 --> 27:22.960
in the future?

27:23.660 --> 27:24.500
Oh, right.

27:24.520 --> 27:26.630
Just one final tip I forgot to tell you.

27:26.630 --> 27:28.880
Your coach also proposed
the fourth tactic—

27:28.880 --> 27:30.410
high-intensity pressing.

27:31.310 --> 27:32.200
So Coach Wang did propose a tactic.

27:32.200 --> 27:32.720
Ms. Lin,

27:32.720 --> 27:33.440
why didn't you tell us earlier?

27:33.440 --> 27:34.770
We picked the right one.

27:35.110 --> 27:36.570
One can never go wrong
when one uses his brain.

27:36.570 --> 27:37.850
See? I was right.

27:37.920 --> 27:39.400
We will definitely win!

27:50.030 --> 27:50.830
Kevin.

27:52.110 --> 27:52.960
A word?

27:53.480 --> 27:54.400
Who are you?

27:54.400 --> 27:55.720
Why should I have a word with you?

27:55.720 --> 27:59.980
Let's talk about your four glorious
victories against stronger opponents.

28:01.070 --> 28:02.240
Sorry.

28:02.680 --> 28:03.350
I have a flight to catch.

28:03.350 --> 28:04.750
My ride's arriving soon.

28:05.270 --> 28:07.070
On January 17th last year,

28:07.070 --> 28:08.480
you didn't attend
the club's regular meeting.

28:08.480 --> 28:10.010
Where were you at that time?

28:22.020 --> 28:23.860
Winfred Wang.

28:24.400 --> 28:25.650
It's you?

28:27.000 --> 28:28.030
What do you want?

28:29.640 --> 28:31.300
As I said, just a word with you.

28:32.110 --> 28:33.510
If you won't talk to me,

28:34.030 --> 28:35.890
I'll have to talk to someone else.

28:42.460 --> 28:44.090
What exactly do you want?

28:46.350 --> 28:47.360
Just a deal,

28:48.110 --> 28:49.110
plain and simple.

28:50.730 --> 28:52.400
Winfred Wang,

28:52.510 --> 28:53.750
I know you.

28:54.440 --> 28:57.030
But I remember we've never crossed paths.

28:58.590 --> 28:59.630
Is that so?

28:59.650 --> 29:01.000
Have you forgotten

29:01.070 --> 29:03.670
the match
between Nanton and Hammer years ago?

29:05.920 --> 29:06.780
I don't recall.

29:07.800 --> 29:10.090
Besides, I left Hammer a long time ago.

29:13.750 --> 29:15.210
I'll cut to the chase then.

29:20.720 --> 29:21.790
Inside this, there is

29:21.790 --> 29:24.190
proof of you hiring someone
to frame Jason.

29:25.650 --> 29:27.400
You may choose from two options.

29:27.400 --> 29:28.160
One,

29:28.750 --> 29:31.480
I'll hand this to the police
and you'll go to jail.

29:32.640 --> 29:33.310
Two,

29:36.030 --> 29:37.750
tell me who you hired.

29:38.200 --> 29:39.330
Then I'll let you go.

29:47.070 --> 29:49.270
I don't know what you're talking about.

29:53.960 --> 29:55.040
Really?

29:55.370 --> 29:56.960
I don't mind jogging your memory

29:56.960 --> 29:59.560
about what happened
on January 17th last year.

30:00.680 --> 30:01.880
It was

30:02.400 --> 30:04.110
a rare sunny day that day.

30:05.480 --> 30:08.010
Spade Q said she hates going out
when it rains.

30:08.400 --> 30:09.590
Me too.

30:09.590 --> 30:12.350
It feels good to train
in the rain, though.

30:13.960 --> 30:15.480
It is your judgement

30:15.480 --> 30:18.080
that Spade Q would be more active
on sunny days.

30:19.030 --> 30:20.480
In the half month after the incident,

30:19.480 --> 30:20.820
[January 18, 2024, clear]

30:20.480 --> 30:22.030
there were only five sunny days.

30:20.850 --> 30:22.170
[January 19, 2024, clear]

30:22.200 --> 30:23.290
[January 22, 2024, clear]

30:22.720 --> 30:24.510
And only on the morning of January 17th,

30:23.320 --> 30:24.350
[January 26, 2024, clear]

30:25.790 --> 30:28.250
Kevin bailed on
an important club activity.

30:31.790 --> 30:33.550
This is a map of the London Underground.

30:33.550 --> 30:35.440
Here are all the underground stations.

30:35.440 --> 30:38.300
I found that his hotel
was roughly in this location.

30:38.440 --> 30:40.420
[Wimbledon] [Exeter] [Wandsworth]

30:38.790 --> 30:39.590
These are

30:39.590 --> 30:41.110
the underground stations
near this location.

30:41.110 --> 30:42.840
Let's check them out one by one.

30:45.030 --> 30:48.030
See too far away...

31:09.700 --> 31:10.100
[A variety of food combinations]

31:10.260 --> 31:11.140
[I told Spade Q my lucky number]

31:11.160 --> 31:12.220
[I didn't expect hers
to be the same as mine]

31:12.250 --> 31:13.410
[We coincidentally share
the same lucky number, 19]

31:14.790 --> 31:16.880
I told Spade Q my lucky number.

31:17.480 --> 31:19.070
I didn't expect hers
to be the same as mine.

31:19.070 --> 31:21.930
We coincidentally
share the same lucky number, 19.

31:22.030 --> 31:23.760
It must be a place that requires

31:24.160 --> 31:26.720
no identity verification
or face-to-face contact

31:26.720 --> 31:29.510
for a large cash transaction
to be completed.

31:30.000 --> 31:31.870
The underground station lockers

31:32.270 --> 31:34.350
must be the best choice.

31:47.280 --> 31:48.800
We are only one step away from the truth.

31:48.800 --> 31:50.070
Who would've known those

31:50.070 --> 31:52.540
crappy surveillance cameras
were just for show?

31:52.540 --> 31:53.760
We know this,

31:54.350 --> 31:55.480
but he might not.

31:58.680 --> 31:59.740
Shall we bluff him?

32:01.770 --> 32:02.850
That day,

32:03.750 --> 32:06.960
you were absent from
an important press conference at the club

32:06.960 --> 32:09.220
because of an appointment with someone.

32:10.070 --> 32:11.870
You had to pay a deposit that day.

32:12.070 --> 32:13.240
So you put the cash

32:14.590 --> 32:16.630
in a locker numbered 19

32:16.750 --> 32:18.010
to finish the payment.

32:19.310 --> 32:20.330
Unfortunately,

32:20.680 --> 32:22.210
all the evidence is in here.

32:23.880 --> 32:25.010
That's impossible.

32:26.750 --> 32:29.240
Are you sure
those surveillance cameras were working?

32:29.240 --> 32:30.410
What a coincidence.

32:31.240 --> 32:32.430
Right opposite the locker,

32:32.430 --> 32:35.560
there were hidden cameras
set up by the railway company.

32:45.830 --> 32:47.160
You've lost, Kevin.

32:51.000 --> 32:52.410
Making a deal with me now

32:52.590 --> 32:54.750
is your best and only choice.

32:59.920 --> 33:02.720
No need for me to repeat
the options for you, right?

33:04.750 --> 33:06.030
How can I be sure

33:06.440 --> 33:09.240
that you'll let me go
when you find the mastermind?

33:12.550 --> 33:13.750
You were after money,

33:14.540 --> 33:16.070
but you didn't kill anyone.

33:16.720 --> 33:18.070
I'm looking for the person

33:18.070 --> 33:20.200
who actually drove Jason to a dead end.

33:39.480 --> 33:40.160
I...

33:41.510 --> 33:43.550
I didn't know that kid would die.

33:44.510 --> 33:46.070
Really, believe me.

33:46.550 --> 33:48.270
All I wanted to do
was keep the kid off the field,

33:48.270 --> 33:49.070
so Nanton would lose.

33:49.070 --> 33:50.200
It was just that simple.

33:50.200 --> 33:53.310
-Who would've known that kid...
-Who on earth did you hire?

33:53.310 --> 33:55.070
There was never a face-to-face meeting.

33:55.070 --> 33:57.600
I only communicated
with that person online.

33:57.720 --> 33:58.640
It's true.

33:58.750 --> 34:00.550
I have no idea who he is.

34:00.550 --> 34:01.880
Try to cast your mind back.

34:01.880 --> 34:04.010
Even the slightest detail would help.

34:11.550 --> 34:13.550
What gave me the deepest impression

34:14.659 --> 34:16.320
was that his profile picture.

34:16.810 --> 34:17.960
It was

34:19.280 --> 34:20.540
a butterfly specimen.

34:23.480 --> 34:24.630
I've told you everything I know.

34:24.630 --> 34:25.800
This is all of it.

34:26.110 --> 34:27.110
Really.

34:28.230 --> 34:29.889
As for this USB flash drive...

34:30.000 --> 34:31.070
Hey, you made me a promise.

34:31.070 --> 34:32.000
I-I have told you

34:32.000 --> 34:33.120
everything I know!

34:33.150 --> 34:34.020
Mr. Wang,

34:34.040 --> 34:35.070
leave the rest to me.

34:35.070 --> 34:35.960
Got any clues?

34:36.670 --> 34:37.670
If he knew

34:37.670 --> 34:39.070
we had no solid evidence at all,

34:39.070 --> 34:40.400
would he be infuriated?

34:40.679 --> 34:42.210
Let's get back to Hongjing.

34:42.360 --> 34:42.889
Let's go.

34:51.070 --> 34:51.960
Ms. Lin,

34:51.960 --> 34:54.150
didn't the property management inform you?

34:54.150 --> 34:54.880
Recently,

34:54.880 --> 34:56.920
old residential buildings
in the city are being renovated.

34:56.920 --> 34:57.590
We're required

34:57.590 --> 35:00.000
to examine and repair
the wiring of all these old buildings.

35:00.000 --> 35:01.150
I've just come back.

35:01.150 --> 35:02.920
Maybe the notification
hasn't reached me yet.

35:02.920 --> 35:04.110
All the circuit breakers

35:04.110 --> 35:06.920
in your room are old-fashioned.

35:06.940 --> 35:07.440
Did they

35:07.440 --> 35:08.510
often trip in the past?

35:08.510 --> 35:10.440
Yes, that happened a lot.

35:10.710 --> 35:12.030
I'll first replace

35:12.030 --> 35:13.400
the high-power ones.

35:13.400 --> 35:15.930
Surge voltage has a big impact
on the circuit.

35:16.190 --> 35:17.920
I'd hate to affect the other rooms.

35:17.920 --> 35:18.960
Sorry to trouble you, Ms. Lin.

35:18.960 --> 35:19.630
But could you turn off

35:19.630 --> 35:20.670
all switches in the house now?

35:20.670 --> 35:21.280
Okay.

35:21.280 --> 35:23.940
I'll go turn off the switches
on the third floor.

35:29.760 --> 35:32.160
They should be in the same position,
right?

35:41.900 --> 35:42.720
[The probability of Lin Wanxing
being Spade Q: 0%]

35:47.900 --> 35:49.620
[The probability of Lin Wanxing
being Spade Q: 0%]

35:51.070 --> 35:53.670
[This year's top college entrance exam
scorer has been announced]

35:55.610 --> 35:56.410
[Rising star falls!]

35:56.440 --> 35:58.470
[Nanton's most promising Chinese
footballer reportedly dies of suicide]

36:11.520 --> 36:11.980
[I can tell that you like rainy days best]

36:12.010 --> 36:12.480
[Maybe you won't hate rainy days anymore]

36:12.510 --> 36:13.080
[I'll teach you how to catch fireflies
with a bottle next time]

36:13.100 --> 36:14.330
[Just like my mom. But she passes the buck
when I perform poorly academically]

36:14.360 --> 36:15.500
[There's a psychological term
called anticipatory anxiety]

36:15.530 --> 36:16.460
[I had a dream about being expelled,
where the teacher said I was dragging]

36:16.490 --> 36:17.600
[the entire class down.
It felt so real]

36:17.630 --> 36:18.630
[Which are more appealing to you,
sneakers with mushroom]

36:18.650 --> 36:19.750
[or beautiful fireflies?]

36:19.770 --> 36:21.130
[I can't believe there are
such beautiful fireflies in the U.K.]

36:26.380 --> 36:27.110
[Rising star falls!]

36:27.140 --> 36:29.520
[Nanton's most promising Chinese
footballer reportedly dies of suicide]

36:36.860 --> 36:39.800
[The probability of Lin Wanxing
being Spade Q: 0%]

36:55.320 --> 36:57.150
-Come huddle.
-Come on.

36:58.550 --> 36:59.410
We'd better not

36:59.590 --> 37:01.550
let the coach down though he's not around.

37:01.550 --> 37:02.480
Ms. Lin, don't forget

37:02.480 --> 37:05.410
to capture our glory in video
and send it to the coach.

37:06.710 --> 37:07.650
Ms. Lin,

37:08.110 --> 37:09.320
the floor's all yours.

37:09.320 --> 37:11.230
Say something inspiring.

37:17.670 --> 37:18.670
Ms. Lin,

37:18.670 --> 37:19.920
you've got really dark circles
under your eyes.

37:19.920 --> 37:22.780
Did you not sleep well
for worrying about the match?

37:23.630 --> 37:24.440
I'm fine.

37:24.960 --> 37:26.920
Do you remember our strategy?

37:27.030 --> 37:27.880
Of course.

37:27.880 --> 37:29.680
It's high-intensity pressing.

37:29.960 --> 37:32.360
Exactly. We chose that tactic together.

37:32.750 --> 37:35.410
Have faith in it.
Also, have faith in ourselves.

37:35.480 --> 37:37.940
You've got this.
We'll surely win the match.

37:38.840 --> 37:39.840
Come on!

37:41.840 --> 37:42.590
Come on.

37:42.590 --> 37:42.860
Hands here.

37:42.860 --> 37:44.190
-Come on.
-Here it goes.

37:49.000 --> 37:50.190
Hongjing No. 8 High School!

37:50.190 --> 37:52.400
-We've got this!
-Let's go for it!

37:53.210 --> 37:53.980
-Brilliant.
-Done.

37:53.980 --> 37:54.840
-Let's go.
-Go.

37:59.730 --> 38:02.440
[Yongchuan Provincial Youth Super League]

38:02.470 --> 38:04.810
[Hongjing No. 8 High School
versus Yuzhou Yinxiang]

38:03.840 --> 38:04.670
Hello, everyone in the audience.

38:04.670 --> 38:06.400
Welcome to the Youth Super League

38:06.400 --> 38:07.550
right here at the venue.

38:07.550 --> 38:08.590
Today's match will be held

38:08.590 --> 38:11.190
between Hongjing No. 8 High School
and Yuzhou Yinxiang.

38:11.190 --> 38:12.280
Now, we can see the players

38:12.280 --> 38:13.880
of both teams have already

38:13.880 --> 38:15.190
gotten onto the field.

38:13.950 --> 38:20.480
[Hongjing No. 8 High School]
[Yuzhou Yinxiang] [Live broadcasting]

38:15.190 --> 38:17.320
The referee is ready as well.

38:17.320 --> 38:19.510
A fierce battle is about to unfold.

38:26.810 --> 38:29.500
[Hongjing No. 8 High School]
[Yuzhou Yinxiang] [Live broadcasting]

38:33.550 --> 38:34.400
Mind the back!

38:46.030 --> 38:46.760
Come on.

38:46.760 --> 38:47.630
The trunk, please.

38:47.630 --> 38:50.590
Hello, the number you dialed
is powered off.

38:50.590 --> 38:51.550
Please try again later.

38:51.550 --> 38:52.510
How about this?

38:53.590 --> 38:54.110
You take this cab.

38:54.110 --> 38:54.840
I'll take the one behind.

38:54.840 --> 38:55.630
Let's split up.

38:55.630 --> 38:56.110
Okay.

38:56.500 --> 38:56.950
Come.

38:57.480 --> 38:58.840
Sir, pop the trunk, please. Thanks!

38:58.840 --> 38:59.630
Where to, handsome?

38:59.630 --> 39:01.070
No. 444, Tongtian Road.

39:02.110 --> 39:03.230
Going to the stadium to watch a match?

39:03.230 --> 39:03.800
Yes, a football match.

39:03.800 --> 39:04.930
Okay. Get in the cab.

39:11.670 --> 39:13.920
There are only three minutes left
in the first half.

39:13.920 --> 39:15.230
-Bro.
-It's so intense on the field.

39:15.230 --> 39:16.710
Are you watching the match?

39:16.710 --> 39:17.880
Turn up the volume please.

39:17.880 --> 39:18.800
I enjoy watching football games too.

39:18.800 --> 39:19.880
Using the high-intensity pressing strategy

39:19.880 --> 39:21.610
to gain possession of the ball.

39:23.630 --> 39:25.290
[Hongjing No. 8 High School]
[Yuzhou Yinxiang] [Live broadcasting]

39:23.840 --> 39:26.550
Throughout the entire first half,

39:26.550 --> 39:27.280
Hongjing has been

39:27.280 --> 39:29.320
taking the initiative on the field,

39:29.320 --> 39:31.110
with multiple chances to score the goal.

39:31.110 --> 39:33.150
But they've never succeeded,
despite such overwhelming presence.

39:33.150 --> 39:34.670
If they can manage to score a goal

39:34.670 --> 39:36.800
in the final moments of the first half,

39:36.800 --> 39:38.920
it will be of great help
for the second half.

39:37.980 --> 39:39.880
[Hongjing No. 8 High School]
[Yuzhou Yinxiang] [0:0]

39:38.920 --> 39:40.920
Now, the game is still scoreless.

39:43.510 --> 39:44.320
Good shot!

39:45.280 --> 39:47.670
Here's a new chance
for Hongjing to attack.

39:47.670 --> 39:48.360
Qin Ao has got the ball

39:48.360 --> 39:50.840
with his back to two opposing defenders.

39:50.840 --> 39:52.440
Chen Jianghe is bursting forward.

39:52.440 --> 39:55.170
Qin Ao makes a pass to Chen Jianghe
as he goes down.

39:55.670 --> 39:58.070
Chen Jianghe breaks through
one opponent after another,

39:58.070 --> 39:59.590
and passes the ball back to Qin Ao.

39:59.590 --> 40:01.440
Under pressure
from two opposing defenders,

40:01.440 --> 40:03.710
Qin Ao strikes the ball
with his left foot!

40:03.710 --> 40:06.000
The ball hits the crossbar!

40:06.000 --> 40:08.110
-The first half is over.
-It's fine.

40:08.110 --> 40:09.320
Hongjing just missed

40:09.320 --> 40:12.120
the best opportunity
in the first half of the game!

40:16.880 --> 40:18.940
Handsome, is the first half over now?

40:20.190 --> 40:21.880
I felt it was pretty intense.

40:22.590 --> 40:24.880
By the way, which team
are you rooting for?

40:24.880 --> 40:26.110
I'm all for Hongjing.

40:26.880 --> 40:28.340
Sir, please drive faster.

40:28.510 --> 40:29.280
Sure.

40:38.230 --> 40:39.000
Sorry.

40:39.550 --> 40:40.360
I'm late.

40:52.320 --> 40:53.110
Quicker!

40:58.800 --> 40:59.760
Over here!

41:09.880 --> 41:10.810
Put up a defense!

41:16.920 --> 41:18.070
-What was that about?
-Referee!

41:18.070 --> 41:18.590
Referee,

41:18.590 --> 41:20.450
that was an obvious pulling foul.

41:40.280 --> 41:41.680
Get closer to each other.

42:01.480 --> 42:02.070
Has anyone guessed

42:02.070 --> 42:03.930
what I'm going to teach you today?

42:03.960 --> 42:04.630
H-How

42:04.630 --> 42:05.690
to make free kicks.

42:06.400 --> 42:07.600
Indirect free kicks.

42:07.760 --> 42:09.000
To be accurate,

42:09.960 --> 42:11.070
it's about four-dimensional free kicks.

42:11.070 --> 42:11.610
Four-dimensional?

42:11.610 --> 42:14.010
-Four-dimensional?
-Four-dimensional?

42:14.230 --> 42:15.280
A four-dimensional free kick

42:15.280 --> 42:17.610
involves a combination of space and time.

42:18.550 --> 42:21.070
Fu Xinshu, Chen Jianghe, Qin Ao,

42:21.070 --> 42:22.630
the three of you will coordinate

42:22.630 --> 42:24.070
to execute our spatial tactics.

42:24.070 --> 42:25.320
Qi Liang,

42:25.320 --> 42:27.520
you'll carry out our temporal tactics.

42:31.150 --> 42:33.000
Fu Xinshu, Chen Jianghe, Qin Ao,

42:33.800 --> 42:34.840
the three of you will launch attacks

42:34.840 --> 42:37.110
to force Yinxiang's defense line
to constantly shift

42:37.110 --> 42:39.310
so as to wear down their concentration.

42:41.480 --> 42:42.710
Qi Liang, you will sprint forward

42:42.710 --> 42:44.230
to create offside controversies

42:44.230 --> 42:46.590
to completely disrupt
the opponents' defensive rhythm.

42:46.590 --> 42:48.630
The coordinated movements
among four Hongjing players

42:48.630 --> 42:50.590
have disrupted
Yinxiang's defensive rhythm.

42:50.590 --> 42:51.510
Over here,

42:51.510 --> 42:52.760
open at the near.

42:52.760 --> 42:53.760
The ball goes to the far.

42:53.760 --> 42:54.710
A strike!

42:55.070 --> 42:56.110
Goal!

42:56.110 --> 42:57.320
The match is over.

42:57.320 --> 42:58.840
Congratulations to Hongjing

42:58.840 --> 42:59.920
for winning the game

42:59.920 --> 43:01.840
with a score of 1-0.

43:01.840 --> 43:04.360
That free kick just now
was absolutely brilliant.

43:04.360 --> 43:06.960
From struggling to tie their first match,

43:06.960 --> 43:09.190
to winning their second by assuming
the defensive before offensive,

43:09.190 --> 43:11.670
and to initiating attacks today,

43:11.670 --> 43:13.510
they've shown steady progress
in three matches.

43:13.510 --> 43:16.150
Hongjing has become the biggest dark horse
of the Youth Super League

43:16.150 --> 43:17.440
in this season.

43:17.440 --> 43:18.670
Let's look forward

43:18.670 --> 43:22.110
to the surprises they'll bring us
in the future!

43:23.670 --> 43:24.230
Dear viewers,

43:24.230 --> 43:25.920
this concludes the broadcast of today's

43:25.920 --> 43:27.110
Youth Super League match.

43:27.110 --> 43:29.400
See you in the next match!

43:56.020 --> 43:57.300
♪ There's nothing to fear ♪

43:58.490 --> 43:59.820
♪ Because you're with me ♪

44:02.970 --> 44:04.220
♪ The light shimmers ♪
